{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"f1sy95vvl2cyfpto8miwxhh","title":"Styling","desc":"","updated":1687492228230,"created":1687489668726,"custom":{},"fname":"web-components.styling","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"0d20dd79f3c47e4997aa8a3b3ffad29e","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"web-components.styling","id":"f1sy95vvl2cyfpto8miwxhh","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"web-components.styling.css-custom-properties","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":12,"offset":12},"end":{"line":2,"column":60,"offset":60},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"web-components.styling.css-custom-properties"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"web-components.styling","id":"f1sy95vvl2cyfpto8miwxhh","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"web-components.Apis.shadow-dom","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":63,"offset":63},"end":{"line":2,"column":97,"offset":97},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"web-components.Apis.shadow-dom"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"web-components.styling","id":"f1sy95vvl2cyfpto8miwxhh","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"https://getbem.com/introduction/","alias":"BEM","position":{"start":{"line":12,"column":210,"offset":487},"end":{"line":12,"column":250,"offset":527},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"https://getbem.com/introduction/"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"web-components.styling","id":"f1sy95vvl2cyfpto8miwxhh","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"web-components.styling.css-encapsulation","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1,"offset":1022},"end":{"line":26,"column":45,"offset":1066},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"web-components.styling.css-encapsulation"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"web-components.styling","id":"f1sy95vvl2cyfpto8miwxhh","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"web-components.styling.css-custom-properties","position":{"start":{"line":29,"column":1,"offset":1196},"end":{"line":29,"column":49,"offset":1244},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"web-components.styling.css-custom-properties"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"web-components.styling","id":"f1sy95vvl2cyfpto8miwxhh","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"web-components.styling.css-parts-api","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":1,"offset":1491},"end":{"line":32,"column":41,"offset":1531},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"web-components.styling.css-parts-api"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"web-components.styling","id":"f1sy95vvl2cyfpto8miwxhh","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"web-components.styling.slotted-elements","position":{"start":{"line":34,"column":76,"offset":1608},"end":{"line":34,"column":119,"offset":1651},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"web-components.styling.slotted-elements"}}],"anchors":{"estilos-globales":{"type":"header","text":"Estilos globales","value":"estilos-globales","line":10,"column":0,"depth":1}},"children":["5vihc22zv3ux3lduf3aaab6","fcj7t4u5hm6t7amh45uid1n","lgs19vv9v8nq2megefqyprn","3lzfo9vm01y09nvjbji1g25"],"parent":"zkfccjgcs7b7pqvirwby57p","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"styling\">Styling<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#styling\"></a></h1>\n<p>Utilizando <a href=\"/notes/5vihc22zv3ux3lduf3aaab6\">CSS Custom Properties</a> y <a href=\"/notes/efwvmwe8ctv925mkt5wrl5z\">shadow-dom</a> podemos crear temas y estilar nuestros componentes.</p>\n<h1 id=\"estilos-globales\">Estilos globales<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#estilos-globales\"></a></h1>\n<p> Uno de los puntos malos del CSS es que por default, el CSS es global. </p>\n<pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">h1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n <span class=\"token property\">color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token color\">red</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n</code></pre>\n<p> Esta regla hace que <strong>todos</strong> los <code>h1</code> sean rojos. Muchas veces solo queremos aplicar una regla a un componente o vista especifico. Para hacer esto en el pasado se utilizaban convenciones de nombres como <a title=\"Private\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"private\">BEM (Private)</a>, para poder evitar que accidentalmente se pisaran estilos. Por ejemplo</p>\n<pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">h1<span class=\"token class\">.article-heading</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n <span class=\"token property\">color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token color\">blue</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token selector\">h1<span class=\"token class\">.article-heading</span> <span class=\"token class\">.article-heading--green</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n <span class=\"token property\">color</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token color\">green</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n</code></pre>\n<p> De esta forma se evita que el estilo impacte en todos los h1 y solo en el que tiene la clase. Esto es mejor pero no es escalable ya que es posible que en proyectos grandes nos encontremos con colisiones en los nombres.</p>\n<p> Con Web Componenst podemos usar el Shadow DOM para simplificar como escribimos CSS.\n<a href=\"/notes/fcj7t4u5hm6t7amh45uid1n\">CSS Encapsulation</a></p>\n<p>Pero ¿Qué ocurre si queremos pisar los estilos del componente? Tal vez para usar un tema custom. Para esto nos van a servir las\n<a href=\"/notes/5vihc22zv3ux3lduf3aaab6\">CSS Custom Properties</a></p>\n<p>Mientras que las CSS Custom Properties permiten una mejor customización del componente y los temas, todavía puede haber veces en las que necesitemos más flexibilidad y debamos activar el estilo de elementos del DOM enteros en nuestro componente\n<a href=\"/notes/lgs19vv9v8nq2megefqyprn\">CSS Parts API</a></p>\n<p>Por ultimo nos queda ver como estilar componentes dentro de nuestros slots <a href=\"/notes/3lzfo9vm01y09nvjbji1g25\">Slotted Elements</a></p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Children</strong>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/5vihc22zv3ux3lduf3aaab6\">CSS Custom Properties</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/fcj7t4u5hm6t7amh45uid1n\">CSS Encapsulation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/lgs19vv9v8nq2megefqyprn\">CSS Parts API</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/3lzfo9vm01y09nvjbji1g25\">Slotted Elements</a></li>\n</ol>","noteIndex":{"id":"guomymvu5xxkrbvedoncjdw","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1687553787663,"created":1687478467553,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"cb6d2289d9babdad43709e4ff265bef2","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"guomymvu5xxkrbvedoncjdw","vaultName":"docs"},"value":"https://webcomponent.dev/","alias":"Cory Rylan","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":94,"offset":117},"end":{"line":4,"column":134,"offset":157},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"https://webcomponent.dev/"}}],"anchors":{"web-components-docs":{"type":"header","text":"Web Components DOCS","value":"web-components-docs","line":8,"column":0,"depth":1}},"children":["zkfccjgcs7b7pqvirwby57p"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"\n# Web Components DOCS\n\nEsta es una documentación de web components basada en el libro *Web Component Essentials* de [[Cory Rylan|https://webcomponent.dev/]]\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true,"enableSelfContainedVaults":true},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":true,"vaultSelectionModeOnCreate":"smart","leaveTrace":false,"bubbleUpCreateNew":true,"fuzzThreshold":0.2}},"randomNote":{},"insertNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"none","enableMultiSelec